        <headline>Flood Watch issued July 30 at 9:44PM EDT until August 1 at 2:00PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues to be
possible.

* WHERE...A portion of northwestern Connecticut, including the
following areas, Northern Litchfield and Southern Litchfield.

* WHEN...From Thursday afternoon through Friday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Excessive runoff may result in flooding of rivers,
creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations.
Flooding may occur in poor drainage and urban areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- A widespread rainfall with periods of heavy rain Thursday
afternoon into Friday morning that could result in localized
flooding. Rainfall amounts range between 1 to 3 inches with
locally higher amounts between 3 to 5 possible.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>You should monitor later forecasts and be alert for possible Flood
Warnings. Those living in areas prone to flooding should be prepared
to take action should flooding develop.</instruction>
